text:
The villa itself was stunning, and the staff were also very helpful and friendly. In particular two of the staff members called Erik, and Nyeoman were very hospitable and helpful. Also a special mention to Anna and Lin who are also very lovely!

Upon arrival we were picked up promptly at the airport and then taken straight up to the villa (Allegia) to sign some papers and conclude some payments. There were refreshing towels ready, and welcome drinks ready as soon as we sat down in the lounge area. The rooms were good, but only one of the rooms have a bath tub (only master bedroom, it would be good if they state this in their villa description.) We travelled as a party of 8 (4 couples) so you could imagine the diplomacy that opened up for that bath tub..
They kept the villa very clean, the villa always looked spotless because of the staff work ethic. The breakfast was prepared for you in the villa every morning and they have a very good selection. 

One of the things you must do if you choose to stay here is the BBQ! The BBQ wasn't what I had in mind, coming from the UK I thought it would be a simple grill, everybody sits around and has a few drinks, but this was like a private dining experience. Everything was cooked there and then for you, they had 2-3 staff members working and serving the whole time. The BBQ really impressed me, thank you Temple Hill for making our first visit to Bali a great one!

The only reasons why I didn't give this 5 stars:
- The bath tub took almost two hours to fill in the Allegia villa, and the handles are loose and broken. Quite disappointed because one of the reasons why we picked Temple Hill was because of the bath tub. When we told the staff about this they said they couldn't fix it because of it would be a big maintenance job. The alternative they told us was "to use the shower head and put the water in the tub using this", this is actually what we did before they suggested it. I was disappointed that they didn't offer anything else, if they had a villa that had a working bath tub that would of been very helpful and nice.

- We also had an issue where we weren't picked up on time. We went to a private beach club and told them 2 hours before the pick-up time (they request a 1 hour notice before actual pick-up time) and the driver came an hour late. When the driver was 15 minutes late we decided to call Temple Hill they said the driver was 20 minutes away, so we decided to wait and hold off on the taxi. However, the driver actually arrived 40 minutes after that phone call. That was very frustrating because they ended up making us late to a dinner reservation, and they also still made us pay for the ride (deducted 50%). They said the issue was traffic, but as a company they should be compensating for the traffic, there really isn't an excuse for being an hour late.

Supermarket and good restaurants across the road from the complex with a good variety to choose from. Breakfast prepared for you in the room each morning was a very nice touch. 
No washing machine at the villas but it wasn't necessary as the complex laundry service is very good and cheap. 
Outdoor lounge chairs in all the villas to relax next to the pool with your own drinks. 
The complex staff go out of their way to make you feel special.
Highly recommend.  
It is not close to the beach but you can get dropped off by the free shuttle service that the complex run for local trips. You can pay for a taxi to the tourist beaches which cost only 70000 rupiah.

Really beautiful villa, spacious, well appointed.  Fantastic staff, really helpful.  The Italian restaurant next door is awesome.  
the shuttle services was really handy.  The beach is an easy 15 minute walk away.  So many positives at this property - a few small issues that you might like to consider.

2.  Room service on one occasion took well over an hour and we had to chase it up.  Not ideal.

3.  People have commented about the school and what appears to be morning prayer.  We heard it but it wasn't offensive.  And the kids that frequent the area are adorable and friendly.

4.  The hot water in our villa took around 5 minutes to arrive.  And that's only when you turn on all hot taps in the bathroom.

5.  The breakfasts (included in the price for us) were a little on the small side.  

Even so, I don't want to detract from what we thought was a wonderful experience.  My partner and I both agree that, if the occasion fit, we would go back.

text:
There are 2 parts to my review, the good and not so good. We stayed in 3 bedroom Villa Santai. First the good. The staff are great, they keep the place very clean and tidy and serve up a big breakfast (actually too much food, we told them to prepare less). The pool is lovely and poolside nice for relaxing, with lots of sun and shade. The bedrooms are large, and the beds comfy. The free wifi is good. The ground floor lounge is large and comfy and nice for watching a DVD in.  Now the not so good. I'd guess the villas are between 10-15 years old and it shows. My first impression was the paint peeling in sheets off the stonework above the front entrance and support pillars around the pool. In my tour of the villa, I was shown all rooms and all floors. The outdoor wooden deck on the roof floor is in very poor condition and that area should only be used with care. I picked out several protruding nails and screws which would have cut your bare feet with my fingernails. There are many loose boards and thus an uneven floor full of trip hazards. The support beams are rotten so new screws can't grip, and it needs replaced asap before someone gets hurt. In the ground floor master bedroom, I thought we had no hot water. But it turns out you need to let it run for between 5 and 10 minutes before you get hot. After a long hot day touring, or afternoon at the beach and you just want to jump in for a quick shower, you can't. Unless you want a cold one. In the upstairs bathroom, water runs piping hot within 30 secs. This needs to be sorted. The DVD players are not multi region. We found one of 2 players would play Balinese or Malaysian "night market" quality DVD's but not genuine UK bought ones. Normally a cheap and cheerful basic Samsung/Sony DVD player will play everything. A bit annoying given we had planned to catch up on some series. One DVD player would not play anything. The lounge has a modern Sony 40" LED TV but could easily use a larger screen.  Lastly, there is a lovely Bose Sound Dock which would be great to play music while you laze by the pool. Unfortunately its for the old Apple connector so if you have an iPhone 5/6 or latest ipod, it cant be used unless you bring an adaptor. 

All that said we enjoyed the stay but the owners really need to spend some money on the fabric. The great staff can't compensate for the lack of upkeep.  Its USD $550/night in August and billed as luxury.  The first large villa as you enter, opposite the reception is actually derelict and almost looks abandoned. Its as if an upgrade was started then just stopped. Overgrown with weeds, ripped apart and looks awful. I don't understand this at all. Its an easy 10 minute walk to the beach albeit down a busy main road. The shuttle is well worth using. There is a large buldiing going up opposite the Villas; maybe another mall that Jimbaran doesn't need. There are already empty new malls. For a change of breakfast, try the excellent Coffee and Grind on the way to the beach in the very quiet Jimbaran Corner mall. The Chocolate Cafe is also very good for meals. I hope the owners take note of client reviews and maybe take some action to make this villa as good as it can be - again.
title: Great staff but villa seriously needs maintenance

As said, this villa is nice but  a small face up would be good by simple painting and oil on the wooden parts. 
In the villa you will get the breakfast prepare in the kitchen by a Chef coming and you have one/two butlers working cleaning the whole day. They are very service minded and will help you in the best way. You can order massage to the villa, this villa has an own massage room and that is really good. You have some good restaurants close by, the Pepenero is on the same area as Temple hill and a good Italian restaurant. The managment also provide free transportation in the Jimbaran area and that is excellent. We ordered the BBQ to our villa the last night, it was so well prepared with candles around the pool. title: Temple Hill Kim-My Villa Loved It and we will be back

text: Temple Hill is a group of villas next to each other which was perfect for my family as there was over 16 of us! All the villas at Temple Hill have the same layout but different decor. We thoroughly enjoyed our stay there. The staff were fantastic, always offering us help when we needed. The chef made breakfast for us every morning in our villa.  Nice view of the ocean from the second floor. Only complaint was the weak internet connection but that's a problem all over Bali. Overall, a fantastic place and I'd definitely stay there again.

text: 4 bedroom bungalow. Absolutely outstanding. Great rooms, fantastic swimming pool and great staff. Highly recommended  and would certainly return. Housekeeping excellent and fantastic restaurant 5 minute walk
title: Excellent

text: Truly a great find. Our plane got delayed and had to find a place quickly. A short 20 min ride from the airport and we were met by the friendliest staff. We were upgraded to a huge three bed villa which is amazing. Such an unexpected great way to finish a holiday.

text: We booked a villa for two nights but we actually had a late flight the second revenging . So we don’t know if it was because of this but we were upgraded to a four bedroom upon arrival. I’ve genuinely never seen in anything like it our jaws nearly hit the floor. It was absolutely huge and stunning in every aspect. The Balinese are the nicest people I’ve came across anyway and it was no different here. The friendliness and service were second to none. I was given a WhatsApp prior to arrival and Oka went out of her way to see to any request. We had not only a floating breakfast but a floating lunch which were both amazing. When we return to Bali. We’ll be back for sure. We literally couldn’t fault a single thing. A massage on the day bed is a must. It was heaven.

text:
Superb from start to finish. 4 bedroom Vila with huge pool, immaculately clean and tidy with great quality beds and linen. Nothing is too mush trouble for any of the staff who are all superb. Great complex over road with several good restaurants.
Would definitely make an effort to come back here
title: There is a reason this is rated so highly!

text: Temple Hill is AMAZING!!! I would recommend it to anyone visiting Bali. Great Location, Staff are amazing, and Villas are superb. A beautiful Villa, amazing pool and close to everything. Will definitely visit again.
title: Amazing!! Must visit!

text:
Booked a two bedroom villa for a family with three kids. At arrival we were upgraded to the 3 bedroom villa “Santai”(with one bedroom locked). The villa was super spacious with 3 floors. It had one large bedroom downstairs with en-suite bathroom & outdoor tub (which we did not use as we had the big pool just right outside). Also downstairs by the pool area is the kitchen and lounge room. The super friendly staff spoiled us with outdoor breakfast here every morning, which you picked on a menu the day before. Plenty to pick from.

Second floor had two additional bedrooms, and the one we used also with en-suite bathroom, additional outdoor shower, and a big veranda with gazebo.

Third floor had a large living room area and roof terrace with view of the bay. Nice afternoon sun when the sun by the pool does not reach over the walls late afternoon. However, we did not spend too much time up here as first floor was the main area. You can stay many people in this villa and still find a quiet place. Really spacious and in great shape. Pool area was fantastic and also had an outdoor shower.

Staff was fantastic and super attentive. Took care of all daily chords and really spoil you and make you feel relaxed. We had two appointed for our villa and they came twice a day cleaning and making breakfast. So nice and friendly.

The Jimbaran area is close to the local people if you compare to for example Nusa Dua which has only resorts. Here you find the mix and you find the lovely Balinese people in every corner. Just across the street is a small center with restaurants and grocery store, and to get down to the beach you can enjoy the free shuttle service which was convenient. A dinner in the beach is recommended, and the sunset is really nice. 

I can only recommend Temple Hill villas as one stop of your Bali experience. For us a four day stay was perfect as we wanted a variety and different locations.
title: Enjoyable stay

text: We have just finished our second visit to Temple Hill all I can say is WOW booked again for next year.We were 3 couples all family members . Thank you to Made and Sari our villa attendants . Reception Lin,Oka,Ana , who are also helpful and attentive .We booked directly with Temple Hill and got an awesome deal,massages are the best everyone who had then loved them.Villa is spotlessly clean ,yummy breakfast,nightly turn down service . Huge pool nothing is too much trouble.We had a yummy in house BBQ we also order a suckling pig ,as it was my sister in laws birthday celebration.We used the free Jimbaran transport provided by Temple Hill ,we also went to OPIA for a beautiful dinner food and views outstanding  if you book through reception you get 10% discount.What more can l say so relaxing shopping centre across the road great supermarket for all your supplies ,coffee shop ,doughnut shop so good.THANK YOU Temple Hill see you next year 👍💕💕
title: THANK YOU TEMPLE HILL  🙏 BEAUTIFUL HOLIDAY AGAIN ❤️❤️❤️

text:
From the moment we got there to the moment we left we were in awe of this place. It's truely a gem, a piece of paradise and every time I walked in the front door and saw the pool I smiled. 
We stayed in the santai and it was beautiful. Breakfast was a great touch and many choices were offered. 
The only thing I would say is the shower needs a double one or a bigger rain head because it was a little hard to share. Also the bath tub water wasn't hot enough for me, I like hot baths. 
The taxi service around jimbaran for free was awesome. 
The massage that was offered was ok but would be improved with music. 
The in house movies were nice. 
The villa had modern furniture and was lay out really well. 
Staff were always friendly and helpful and always had a smile on their face and greeted us. 
First time in a villa and would never go back to hotel stays. 
The villa is a little expense but I assure you it's money worth spending. 
A cute little touch was they came in if we were going to be out after dark and turn the lights on for us. 
We will be back. Thank you temple hill
title: Most amazing place ever !

text:
Temple Hill Residence Villa is ideally located in Jimbaran ; not by the beach though, but slightly remote so you can enjoy calm & tranquility and be at walking distance from the sea still.

The complex offers a great range of luxury villas, all beautifully furnished and featuring a huge private pool. The service staff is very professional, which adds a little bonus to the experience.
It's the perfect place for a one-week stay with a bunch of good friends. The villas are fully equipped (kitchen, living room, pondok, etc.), all bedrooms have enclosed bathrooms and some have bathtub + shower.
Breakfast is included in the rate, prepared and served at your villa, at the time you set in prior.
Plus : the upper villas offer a perfect view over Jimbaran bay !

Service also include a free shuttle within Jimbaran area. Book it in advance, in case it's already booked by other guests.

Well, to sum up, it's a little paradise away from the crowd.
title: Little peace haven away from the crowd

text:
I have stayed at a few villas in Bali. While Temple Hill looks nice and has a great layout, some of its furnishings require refurbishment such as the sliding doors (mine hard to close) and wear and tear. The parquet floors were polished so well they were slippery! I almost slipped a few times and so did my friends! The breakfast choices were great and the staff were very friendly and accommodating. In all, a nice villa for group stays.
title: Average villa but excellent service

text: My husband, myself and 2 other couples stayed for a week....and it was by far the best week. The villa was great and it had all the comforts you could ask for, it was very clean and very comfortable. The in Villa breakfast was fabulous, you pick what you wanted from the menu and your own chef comes along and cooks it for, now that's service. They even made a cake one morning for one of our fellow travellers who celebrated her Birthday while at the villa. The service from the staff was fast and efficient. One of our air con units stopped working, with in 10 min they where fixing it and it was working like new. If your after a Villa experience like know other I would highly recommend Temple Hill, not a bad word to say...thankyou Anna and staff your all fabulous, and we will be back for sure.
title: Best Villa Experience!

text:
We stayed at a 3 bedroom villa at Temple Hill in December. The staff (Anna and the troops) was excellent on the whole, with just a few hiccups. Arriving from a 2 hour-long wait at the airport with 2 kids under 2 years, with an absent airport pick-up service, the holiday did not bode well at the beginning. But Temple Hill staff managed to remedy the situation with a warm welcome. Anna, the manager spoke English well and saw to our needs well.
The Villa has an Italian restaurant, PeppeNero, just a minute's walk from the main gate. It serves decent food with a magnificent view. 
Options for the breakfast was limited to eggs, fried rice (Indonesian style), cereal and fruits. Fresh juices were also on the menu but I would advice against the OJ - it is a cordial and NOT fresh. 
The doors of the room were just 3 steps away from a 1.5 metre pool which was not ideal with 2 young children but it did provide much entertainment. 
Honestly, I have had better villa experiences in Bali and Temple Hill is not one which takes my breathe away.
title: Awesome service, but an ok villa experience.

text: We spent 4 nights in one of the 4 bedroom Temple Hill villas back in early September. The villa was very spacious and clean and the pool lovely and cool. The location is ok ie about a 10 min walk to Jimbaren Bay but with small kids this is not really ideal - that said the hotel staff were more than happy to drive you down there free of charge and come back and pick you up. The room set up is not really ideal for small kids because none of the bedrooms are interconnecting and 3 of the 4 open out on to the pool - again not ideal with small children. Breakfast was included in the room rate and it was ok but nothing special - lets just say we spent lots of time at Grocer and Grind! There were a few funny bathroom smells particularly from the upstairs bathroom, we did tell the staff and they cleaned it but I think it was the plumbing! An ok experience but I personally am not sold on the villa experience when you have smaller kids (ie under 5's). Overall a good villa complex with good staff but not sure I need to go back.

title: Villa Kim-my, excellent place and services!!

text:
We had 5 great days in a 3 bed villa (we were upgraded from a 2 bed) walking in on the first day my husband myself and our 2 grownup daughters were gobsmacked at the size and sumptuous space we were to call home for a while. There were 3 enormous bedrooms each with its own luxurious ensuite, and flat screen, 2 outside showers,  an outside bath, 3 outdoor areas to sun in, a view across the bay, a long pool and 2 living areas each with a flat screen, a study,two extra toilets, a huge amazingly well equipped kitchen and dining area. To be honest too much room for 4 of us but it was beautiful and the staff were fantastic serving us delicious breakfast etc
My only regrets - don't order from the Italian restaurant adjacent and be aware that there is a high school next door that starts at 7 or 7.30 but only happy noises! And the wooden floors are v slippery.
Not the safest place for small children.
title: Luxury and space away from hectic Bali

text:
We stayed in the Princess Kim-My villa over Christmas and the New Year 2011/2012. As a party of 5 adults and two children the villa was perfectly sized and we enjoyed every second of our stay. We are seasoned travellers and used to stay in luxury resorts and the Temple Hill are amongst our top performers. 

Staying in any hotel you expect that everything is working and up to the standard promised in the promotional material, things usually are in 4 and 5 star resorts and everything was running smoothly in our villa with no problems at all.

What really makes a difference is the people you meet, they are the face of the hotel. You can buy gold taps and other expensive interiors, but these materialistic properties can never make up for staff that doesn't make you feel welcome.

Everyone we meet at Temple Hill and Anna and our villa staff were at the absolute top of the list of hotel staff we have ever meet. They made us feel genuine welcome and at home and were at all time extremely helpful and attentive.

10 minute walk to the beach and all the seafood restaurants and the PepeNero restaurant on site one minute away. Great food at great prices. Book a table as it is a very popular restaurant.

We can definitely recommend Temple Hill and its staff with all our heart as they have ensured that we had yet another successful and joyful holiday. A great THANKS to all of them.

Ronnie
title: Villa Princess Kim-My, Temple Hill, Jimbaran.

hi

title: a absolute must

text:
Booked 2 villas (amanara and santai) for the 14 of us. Without a doubt, it's been the best bali experience we have ever had ... by a million miles! Temple hill is a true gem! 

The condition of the villas was wonderful. The pictures on the website were very good, but they are nothing as compared to the real thing! The moment I stepped foot in the villa, I literally didnt feel like going out at all! Rooms were clean & spacious, private pool was well-maintained and fairly big, practically the entire villa was HUGE. Breakfast was served on 2nd floor at the outdoor deck which had the most magnificent view! There was one small mix-up when we found that one of the aircon in the room was not cold. Fortunately the staff was attentive and it was fixed by night time. 

The location of the villa is very accessible. It's very near to Uluwatu temple and Nusa Dua. There are many wellknown villas/resorts nearby like Bulgari, Karma, Four Seasons, etc, but at Temple Hill you only need to pay a fraction of the cost. :) From the 2nd floor of the villa you get a view of the beach. There's a fabulous Italian restaurant PEPeNero just next door. It's a must try! Good food at reasonable price (some may even find it inexpensive!). If you are heading back to the villa by taxi, just tell the driver 'Pepenero' ... based on my experience all drivers knew the location. 

The service was super-ultimate-beyond-great-pamperingly-addictive it makes you wanna come back for more! By far the most helpful staff I have ever met (thanks Mba Nadi!). Car (with driver) is available free of charge anytime for a short ride around the hotel area. Useful if you have cravings for midnight snacks or when you're running out of mixers or when you simply wanna go to money exchange. The staff helped us a lot with car bookings (a little more expensive that the rates outside, but you will get cars with much better condition) and even outside restaurants reservation (even made sure they served vegetarian so it would fit to everyone's requirement). Some of us tried the in-house spa and, based on what  I've heard from those who did, it's fabulous. We also had in-villa BBQ dinner during our stay and it was superb!!! They dressed up professionally like any big restaurants' staff would and decorated the villa with LOTS of candles and flowers by the pool it just looked so beautifully unreal. The food was quite good and there was enough and so much more to go for everyone. 

To Ibu Anna, Mba Nadi, and the rest of the team attending to us - thanks so much for hosting us and making our last trip the most unforgettable one. We will sure come back for more! 

H Lim & party
title: Heaven in the Island of Gods

text:
We booked 2 villas in May 2011 for a group of 19 people.  We stayed at 3 hotels/villa during our Bali Trip, but temple hill is definitely the one we enjoyed the most.  There aren't too much comment or pictures online about temple hill, so we were a little bit worried at first too.

There are just too many choices in bali. It took us weeks to look for the perfect villa that fit our budget  and expectation. what make me quickly decide was their quick and helpful response thru email. (even before I booked anything) i would definitely recommend this place to everyone looking for a villa for big groups. ( THANK YOU ANNA for all your help during our 2 days stay)

About the villa, it's quite clean and spacious. The pool was big and the 4 bedrooms villa we stayed had 1 big living room (with nice TV and iPod dock) and an activitiy room. The staff were always very attentive and helpful to our request.
We had a BBQ buffet dinner there, wonderful food and good price (as compared to eating at jimbaran) what impressed us most was they had candles arranged all around the pool (at no extra charge) and twobeautiful heart shaped floating candles at the pool for our party. 

About the room, it is not a brand new hotel but was clean and nice.  Only problem was the shower in the master bedroom dun work well and with little hot water sometimes.  Hotel is also located at a quiet hillside, yet close to nearby attractions by car.

The Internet was fine was no issue at all.  

Anna ( our main contact person there) is the nicest person we met on the whole trip. We decided we wanted to do water sport on the day we check out, it was arranged for us with rides within 15mins and allowed us for late check out. She even recommended and booked spa for us and our friends after we checked out the hotel. Big thank you again, Anna!

However, we are disappointed at the extra 3% charge if paid by credit card. We book thru those big vendor quoted at USD. But realize all Bali hotels would then convert to RP ( using a poor rate ) and charge. So end up we paid 9% more in our local currency ( combining the effect of poor exchange rate and 3% charge at hotel, plus poor rate and 2% overseas spending charges by credit card.) and we didn't incur this 3% charges at other Bali hotels.

Overall it was a super enjoyable stay and value for money and wish we can go back again.

(check out their pictures on their website, very close to actual, I know a lot of hotels don't)

La villa 2 chambres n étant plus disponible on nous a donner une villa 4 chambres ! Juste magique ! Nous n avons la clé que d 1 chambre, la master. Et le salon salle à manger principal. Tout est immense la pièce principale faisant +/- 100m2. Une décoration raffinée. Magnifique.De beaux matériaux.
La chambre immense avec 1 immense salle de bain attenante. Un bain de fleurs nous attendait pour nos 25 ans de mariage.
La piscine immense également se situant au centre de la villa au milieu d 1 végétation travaillée.
Nous avons demandé les services de masseuses à domicile  : après 1 mois dans Bali nous avons eu ici les meilleurs massages balinais pour  220 mille roupies l heure. On a à faire à de vraies professionnelles c est clair.
C est sur que pour 2....C est très très grands mais pour 4 ça l est également. 
Un établissement exceptionnel.
Je ne comprends toujours pas pourquoi il n y a pas d avis datant de 2018....le plus récent trouvé étant de 2017.
Très belle découverte

text: Tout était parfait. Nous avions commandé une villa 2 chambres mais l'équipe nous a fait une surprise et nous a donné une villa 4 chambres! (Villa Amanara) Nous avions donc une gigantesque villa qui pouvait contenir 8 personnes avec une énorme piscine et nous n'étions que 3! La vue depuis la villa donne sur la baie. Même si les villas sont proches de l'aéroport (4km) nous n'avons jamais entendu aucun avion. Les petits déjeuné étaient copieux et délicieux, le personnel adorable, la villa propre, rien a dire. Les villas sont d'ailleurs très bien placées: proches des magasins et de bons restaurants. Pour atteindre la plage de Jimbaran il faut marcher environ 10 minutes mais ça ne nous a pas posé de problème. Donc si vous passez à Jimbaran, ce qui vaut d'ailleurs vraiment le coup, n'hésitez pas et venez au Temple Hill. Vous ne serez pas déçus.
title: Juste parfait!

text:
Wir waren zu sechst in Bali und entschieden uns für diese Unterkunft. Wir hatten eine eine doppelstöckige Villa mit 3 Schlafzimmern, Küche, riesigem Pool mit Megasoundanlage, Whirlpool, Billiardtisch, Lounge-Terrasse im zweiten Stock. Es ist alles sehr modern eingerichtet und auch sehr sauber. Es gab eigentlich nichts zu bemängeln, ausser dass eine Toilette nicht mehr funktionierte und dieses Problem in der ganzen Zeit nicht behoben werden konnte. Es waren aber noch genügend andere Toiletten da. Diese Unterkunft ist wirklich ein Luxus-Traum, den man sich auch als ''Normal''-Verdiener leisten kann. Zudem hatte man noch eigenes Personal, das den ganzen Tag in der Auffahrt auf einen Auftrag wartete.
Sollten Sie also mal in Jimbaran eine Unterkunft suchen, kann ich diese sehr empfehlen. Luxus vom feinsten und das zu erschwinglichen Preisen, v.a.wenn man in einer Gruppe reist, ist der Preis absolut kein Problem.
title: Traumvilla!!!

text: Отличное месторасположение вилл, вдали от дороги и пляжа. Не первая линия, но это даже лучше. Вдоль берега вереницей стоят рестораны, в которых жарят, парят еду при чем на прессованном угле и запах стоит не очень приятный, перебивает запах океана даже и шумновато, так как берег использую для променада. Сами виллы потрясающие, просторные и полностью оборудованны. Уборка и сервис на высшем уровне. Отдельное спасибо персоналу, за отзывчивость и заботу. Наша любимица была ОКА!) приходила на помощь в любых вопросах. Отель предоставляет постояльцам бесплатный трансфер до пляжа и вообще по всему району Джимбаран. Хороший Wi-Fi, что не маловажно. На против резиденции хороший магазин (типографическую Азбуки Вкуса). Всегда свежие овощи фрукты, хорошее мясо и все остальное что нужно для приготовления пищи. Кстати для любителей готовить, на вилле просторная кухня со всеми необходимыми для этого вещами. Вообщем, очень рекомендую !!! У нас была вилла на три спальни.

text:
友人とバリに旅行した際に利用しました。少しお値段はしますが、非常に良い思いをしました。

まず、これはヴィラ形式という、数部屋ある豪邸をグループで貸し切る形式のホテルです。私の宿泊した棟はベッドルーム３部屋にソファのある部屋が一つ、リビングダイニングルーム、キッチン付きで、７〜８名が宿泊できる規模でした。
部屋はおしゃれで清潔ですし、ウェルカムフルーツなども置いてあります。朝食はわざわざ調理してくださる方が棟まで来てくださって、卵料理などを作っていただきました。スタッフの方の対応もとても良かったです。

夕食は、徒歩で行ける場所（ヴィラの正門の横）に一つあります。おそらく観光客しか来ない場所なのでは？と思いますが美味しかったですし、そこまで値段も高くなかったです。

１棟につき１つプールがついていますし、他の棟と少し離れているのでみんなで騒ぐにはとても良いかと思います。大人数の家族旅行、グループ旅行にお勧めです。
